---
import MainLayout from '../../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
---

<MainLayout title="DAG Theory & Data Pipelines">
    <div class="py-12">
        <article class="max-w-3xl">
            <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold gradient-text mb-4">DAG Theory & Data Pipelines</h1>
            <div class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mb-2">Published on June 10, 2026</div>
            <div class="flex gap-2 mb-8 flex-wrap">
                <span class="bg-orange-100 dark:bg-orange-900/30 text-orange-700 dark:text-orange-300 text-xs px-2 py-1 rounded">Data Engineering</span>
                <span class="bg-orange-100 dark:bg-orange-900/30 text-orange-700 dark:text-orange-300 text-xs px-2 py-1 rounded">Airflow</span>
            </div>

            <section class="space-y-6">
                <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold">Understanding Directed Acyclic Graphs</h2>
                <p>DAGs are graphs with directed edges and no cycles. They're fundamental to data pipeline orchestration.</p>
                
                <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold">Apache Airflow and DAGs</h2>
                <p>Airflow lets you define data pipelines as DAGs using Python. Tasks are nodes, dependencies are edges.</p>

                <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold">Building Robust Pipelines</h2>
                <p>Use DAGs to express complex data workflows with clear dependencies, error handling, and monitoring.</p>

                <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold">Topological Sorting</h2>
                <p>Understanding topological sorting helps you optimize task execution and identify parallelization opportunities.</p>
            </section>

            <a href="/blog" class="inline-block mt-12 text-indigo-600 hover:text-indigo-700 font-medium">← Back to Blog</a>
        </article>
    </div>
</MainLayout>
